messages.subject: Newbie with a simple question
messages.msgSnippet: Head lice cannot jump like fleas. They have no wings and cannot fly. Physical contact between people is a common way they spread. Yeah, and they used to
messages.messageBody:
"Head lice cannot jump like fleas. They have no wings and cannot fly.
Physical contact between people is a common way they spread."

Yeah, and they used to infect most of the population. There was a day
when lice were commonplace and not viewed as a big problem.:)
They carry no disease, are not dangerous on any level nor do they
cause any health concerns. They're just a damn nuisance.

Ren
learninginfreedom.com
